00:33:02.000 --> 00:33:06.000
Yeah. Great question, Dennis. We are having conversations about this.

00:33:06.000 --> 00:33:09.000
So right now within positron, there's a publisher extension.

00:33:09.000 --> 00:33:12.000
That publisher extension lets people who have self-managed connect,

00:33:12.000 --> 00:33:15.000
be able to go ahead and deploy these things to, to connect.

00:33:15.000 --> 00:33:19.000
We will eventually become sort of another arm that can come out from that

00:33:19.000 --> 00:33:22.000
kind of extension. But at this, at the moment,

00:33:22.000 --> 00:33:26.000
all we can really do is ingest code from GitHub and then deploy or publish

00:33:26.000 --> 00:33:28.000
these, these, these assets.

00:33:28.000 --> 00:33:31.000
We don't have the ability yet to sort of take files or to take bundles.

00:33:31.000 --> 00:33:33.000
We're working on both of these things simultaneously,

00:33:33.000 --> 00:33:37.000
and we do hope to get in there. I would hope,

00:33:37.000 --> 00:33:39.000
I don't want to put any actual time in there,

00:33:39.000 --> 00:33:41.000
but I would hope by the end of the year that we have sort of an

00:33:41.000 --> 00:33:48.000
alternative publishing flow in addition to the GitHub workflow.

00:33:48.000 --> 00:33:49.000
Okay. From Jeff,

00:33:49.000 --> 00:33:55.000
we've got what sort of content and user access controls are on the roadmap.

00:33:55.000 --> 00:33:58.000
Yeah. So I think from a content perspective,

00:33:58.000 --> 00:34:01.000
I think when you look at a list of what self-managed connect hosts,

00:34:01.000 --> 00:34:04.000
like that goes beyond what we've included in this first iteration.

00:34:04.000 --> 00:34:09.000
So things like voila, I know is, is, is on there.

00:34:10.000 --> 00:34:12.000
As one example, API support,

00:34:12.000 --> 00:34:15.000
like when we were working on positive cloud last year and thinking of APIs,

00:34:15.000 --> 00:34:18.000
like you could, you could work with APIs in the publishing, but like,

00:34:18.000 --> 00:34:19.000
if they're not going,

00:34:19.000 --> 00:34:21.000
you need to be authenticated on that system to bring them in.

00:34:21.000 --> 00:34:23.000
Like we don't have a great story yet for like how people are going to

00:34:23.000 --> 00:34:26.000
manage like 24 seven, always on APIs.

00:34:26.000 --> 00:34:28.000
But I think APIs are something we're thinking of.

00:34:28.000 --> 00:34:30.000
And then there are other frameworks that we'd love to hear more from all of

00:34:30.000 --> 00:34:32.000
you about in terms of which ones you're really using.

00:34:32.000 --> 00:34:34.000
But I think of like panel,

00:34:34.000 --> 00:34:36.000
I think of like adding interactive support for,

00:34:36.000 --> 00:34:41.000
for shiny radio is something that we've heard from,

00:34:41.000 --> 00:34:42.000
from other people as well.

00:34:42.000 --> 00:34:44.000
So like we're considering a lot of these and the more that we hear from you

00:34:44.000 --> 00:34:47.000
specifically on which one, like the easier it makes it for us to sort of

00:34:47.000 --> 00:34:51.000
prioritize bringing some kind of solution into the, into the tools.

00:34:52.000 --> 00:34:55.000
In terms of user access controls we do anticipate again,

00:34:55.000 --> 00:34:58.000
by the end of the year that we're going to have kind of like individual

00:34:58.000 --> 00:35:01.000
accounts where you can have private content.

00:35:01.000 --> 00:35:05.000
And the one thing that is, is for certain in a similar way to shiny apps.io,

00:35:05.000 --> 00:35:08.000
you're going to have the ability to sort of like have a given email out.

00:35:08.000 --> 00:35:11.000
That person will then create an account on connect cloud and be able to

00:35:11.000 --> 00:35:14.000
interact with the application that you gave someone permission for.

00:35:14.000 --> 00:35:17.000
It's not collaboration. They're not going to be working with you.

00:35:17.000 --> 00:35:18.000
They're not part of your account.

00:35:18.000 --> 00:35:21.000
They're just going to be able to see what you want them to be able to see.

00:35:22.000 --> 00:35:24.000
And then getting into next year,

00:35:24.000 --> 00:35:27.000
we're going to start looking more closely at organizational support.

00:35:27.000 --> 00:35:29.000
A lot of that collaboration, you know,

00:35:29.000 --> 00:35:31.000
different roles, different permissions.

00:35:32.000 --> 00:35:36.000
So I expect a lot more of that to start happening in early 2025.

00:35:38.000 --> 00:35:39.000
Very cool.

